## Pull Requests & Review

### Review model tier
Model the code / security / architecture reviewers run on.
- **Live in:** `.claude/skills/pr/SKILL.md` ‚Äî ¬ß1 Pre-flight
- **Current:** session-model (asked per-PR in supervised mode; forced to session-model in unsupervised mode)
- **Options:** session-model ¬∑ opus ¬∑ sonnet ¬∑ haiku ¬∑ fable

### Review scope triage
Threshold below which a small, non-security diff gets code review only (no separate security/architect pass).
- **Live in:** `.claude/skills/pr/SKILL.md` ‚Äî ¬ß4b Review Scope Triage
- **Current:** light review under ~200 changed lines AND no security-sensitive files; full review otherwise
- **Options:** adjust the line threshold; security-sensitive files always force a full review.

### Merge strategy & auto-merge
How a green, reviewed PR is merged.
- **Live in:** `.claude/skills/pr/SKILL.md` ‚Äî ¬ß9
- **Current:** squash + auto-merge (`gh pr merge --squash --auto`), falling back to direct squash merge if auto-merge is disabled on the repo
- **Options:** merge method (squash / merge / rebase) ¬∑ auto vs. manual ¬∑ the ask-before-merge conditions (currently: merge conflicts, major/breaking version, protected branch requiring human approval)

### Deferred-findings policy
Whether non-blocking review findings (`[SUGGESTION]`, `[INFO]`, `[CONCERN]`, `[ADR NEEDED]`) get auto-fixed or only reported.
- **Live in:** `.claude/skills/pr/SKILL.md` ‚Äî ¬ß4b Review Scope Triage ("Deferred-findings policy")
- **Current:** light-review path (small, single-feature diff) auto-fixes `[SUGGESTION]` too; full-review path reports `[SUGGESTION]`/`[INFO]` only; `[CONCERN]`/`[ADR NEEDED]` are always report-only
- **Options:** `light-autofixes-suggestions` (default, above) ¬∑ `always-report-only` (never auto-fix beyond MUST FIX/CRITICAL/HIGH/MODERATE, regardless of diff size) ¬∑ `always-autofix-suggestions` (fix `[SUGGESTION]`/`[INFO]` on every PR, not just the light-review path)

